{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17490995","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17490995"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T05:27:26+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T05:27:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"798"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17582750","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17582750"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T06:54:09+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T06:54:09+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"798"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"798","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/798"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.19,0.11,0.68,0.01,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"798"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92551"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"798","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/798"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"798"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75866"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"1"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"2100"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5602"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"994"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31697"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92551","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/92551"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 21-year-old woman presents for a pre-anaesthetic assessment for left knee reconstruction. She is a professional netballer with a torn left anterior cruciate ligament. Her medical history includes hay fever and asthma. Her medications include regular budesonide and salbutamol puffers.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination she appears well, vitals are within normal limits and no abnormalities are detected.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following most accurately reflects this patient\u0027s ASA score?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["ASA I","ASA IE","ASA II","ASA V","ASA VE"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe American Society of Anaesthesiologists (ASA) designed a scoring system, known as the \u200bASA Physical Status Classification System, which defines the risk of a particular individual who is being planned for a surgical procedure based on their medical co-morbidities.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe classification system is summarised as below:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EASA I \u003C/strong\u003E- A normal healthy patient who is non-smoking and minimal alcohol use\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EASA II\u003C/strong\u003E - A patient with mild systemic disease,\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIncluding current smoker, social alcohol drinker, uncomplicated pregnancy, well-controlled chronic diseases\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EASA \u003C/strong\u003EIII\u003Cstrong\u003E \u003C/strong\u003E- A patient with severe systemic disease\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EASA IV - A patient with severe systemic disease that is a constant threat to life\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EASA \u003Cstrong\u003EV\u003C/strong\u003E - A moribund (i.e. point of death) patient who is not expected to survive without the operation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EASA VI - A declared brain-dead patient whose organs are to be removed for donor purposes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAn \u0027\u003Cstrong\u003EE\u003C/strong\u003E\u0027 can be added to each score, denoting an emergency, where any delay in surgical treatment would lead to a substantial increase in threat to life or body part.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGiven this patient is generally healthy with well-controlled asthma, she would be classified as ASA II.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The \u200bASA Physical Status Classification System defines the risk of a particular individual who is being planned for a surgical procedure based on their medical co-morbidities."],"references":["American Society of Anaesthesiologists - Committee on Economics. \u200bASA Physical Status Classification System [Online]. 2014 [updated 2020 December, cite 2021 February]. Available at: https://www.asahq.org/standards-and-guidelines/asa-physical-status-classification-system","Mayhew D, Mendonca V. Murthy BVS. A review of ASA physical status \u2013 historical perspectives and modern developments. Anaesthesia. 2019;74: 373\u2013379. Available at: https://associationofanaesthetists-publications.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/anae.14569"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75866"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"798"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75866","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/75866"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-18T11:00:50+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-18T11:00:50+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"798"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92551"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"1","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/1"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude34","name":"Anaesthesia","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"65","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/65"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Investigations","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitable for a graduating medical student at the end of their degree","position":1,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"2100","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2100"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Preoperative assessment","synonyms":["Pre-operative assessment","Preoperative evaluation","Pre-operative evaluation"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-01-30T20:59:55+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-11T10:52:19+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"3"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4947","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4947"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\ude7a","name":"Introduction to Clinical Sciences ","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:16:53+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-17T23:16:53+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"14"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"5602","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5602"},"attributes":{"e